* {{ill|Tenpaku Ward|ja|天白区|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenpaku Ward|qq=}} - A ward of Nagoya named after the river.
* {{ill|Tenpaku Village (Aichi)|ja|天白村 (愛知県)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenpaku Village (Aichi)|qq=}} - Formerly in Nagoya, named after the river.
* Tenpaku River - A small river in {{ill|Higashiura Town|ja|東浦町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Higashiura Town|qq=}}, also associated with the Tenpaku deity.<ref>{{Cite book|和書|title=張州府志 第6|year=1916|publisher=名古屋史談会}}</ref>
* {{ill|Tenpaku Town (Okazaki)|ja|天白町 (岡崎市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenpaku Town (Okazaki)|qq=}} - A town in {{ill|Okazaki|ja|岡崎市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Okazaki|qq=}}, named after the Tenpaku deity.
* {{ill|Tenpaku River (Tahara)|ja|天白川 (田原市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenpaku River (Tahara)|qq=}} - A river flowing through {{ill|Tahara City|ja|田原市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tahara City|qq=}}.

=== Mie Prefecture ===
* {{ill|Tenpaku River (Mie)|ja|天白川 (三重県)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenpaku River (Mie)|qq=}} - A river in {{ill|Yokkaichi|ja|四日市市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yokkaichi|qq=}}.
* {{ill|Tenpaku Village (Mie)|ja|天白村 (三重県)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenpaku Village (Mie)|qq=}} - Formerly part of {{ill|Matsusaka|ja|松阪市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsusaka|qq=}}.

