=== Aichi Prefecture ===
* {{ill|Tenpaku River (Aichi)|ja|天白川 (愛知県)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenpaku River (Aichi)|1=Tenpaku River|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11443111}} - A river flowing through {{ill|Nisshin, Aichi|en|Nisshin, Aichi|WD=Q696777|lt=Nisshin|1=Nisshin, Aichi}} and {{ill|Nagoya|en|Nagoya|WD=Q11751|lt=Nagoya|1=Nagoya}}, named after a shrine to Tenpaku deity in its lower reaches.
* {{ill|Tenpaku-ku|en|Tenpaku-ku|WD=Q1155245|lt=Tenpaku Ward|1=Tenpaku-ku}} - A ward of Nagoya named after the river.
* {{ill|Tenpaku Village (Aichi)|ja|天白村 (愛知県)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenpaku Village (Aichi)|1=Tenpaku|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q17177017}} - Formerly in Nagoya, named after the river.
* Tenpaku River - A small river in {{ill|Higashiura|en|Higashiura|WD=Q677745|lt=Higashiura Town|1=Higashiura}}, also associated with the Tenpaku deity.<ref>{{Cite book|和書|title=張州府志 第6|year=1916|publisher=名古屋史談会}}</ref>
* {{ill|Tenpaku Town (Okazaki)|ja|天白町 (岡崎市)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenpaku Town (Okazaki)|1=Tenpaku-chō, Okazaki|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q17218861}} - A town in {{ill|Okazaki, Aichi|en|Okazaki, Aichi|WD=Q242783|lt=Okazaki|1=Okazaki, Aichi}}, named after the Tenpaku deity.
* {{ill|Tenpaku River (Tahara)|ja|天白川 (田原市)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenpaku River (Tahara)|1=Tenpaku River|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q132044415}} - A river flowing through {{ill|Tahara, Aichi|en|Tahara, Aichi|WD=Q501891|lt=Tahara City|1=Tahara, Aichi}}.

